Shawyn Jackson and Angela Jackson sued Cavalier Manufacturing, Inc., d/b/a Buccaneer Homes of Alabama, Inc. (hereinafter \u8220\'3fCavalier\u8221\'3f), alleging negligence, breach of contract, breach of express and implied warranties, and fraud, all in connection with the plaintiffs\rquote  purchase of a mobile home. The plaintiffs complained that the mobile home they purchased from Cavalier contained manufacturing defects. Cavalier filed a motion to dismiss, or in the alternative, a motion to compel arbitration of the plaintiffs\rquote  claims, pursuant to an arbitration clause contained in the \u8220\'3facknowledgment and agreement\u8221\'3f signed by the plaintiffs and by a representative of Cavalier. The trial court, without making any findings of fact, denied Cavalier\rquote s motion. Cavalier appeals.
}
