The dissent states that the Court found no fault with the portion of the arbitration clause that prohibits the arbitrator from awarding punitive damages. That statement is not correct, because this case was remanded \u8220\'3fwith instructions for the trial court to determine whether the arbitration clause is valid even though it prohibits the arbitrator from awarding punitive damages.\u8221\'3f 823 So.2d at 1243.
