The dissent further states that it is based on the belief that the validity of the arbitration agreement should be determined by the trial court, not by the arbitrator. This Court\rquote s opinion is premised upon the principle that the validity of the clause at issue should be determined by the trial court and, in fact, that is the basis upon which this case has been remanded with instructions.
